Below are some example of word tag and wordle, that I have skimmed through:

1. http://bl.ocks.org/ericcoopey/6382449 (D3 Word Cloud implementation by Coopey)
2. http://bl.ocks.org/blockspring/847a40e23f68d6d7e8b5 (D3 Wordcloud by BlockSpring)
3. https://swarbrickjones.wordpress.com/2015/03/16/visualising-reddit-buzzwords-over-time/ (Word cloud over time based on reddit buzzwords)
4. http://static.mrfeinberg.com/bv_ch03.pdf (Creator of Wordle - PDF shows logic behind application)

A very good read regarding drawbacks of word clouds.
1. Word Clouds considered harmful - by Jacob Harris (http://www.niemanlab.org/2011/10/word-clouds-considered-harmful/)

Jason Davies explanation for the word cloud generator (https://www.jasondavies.com/wordcloud/about/)
1. https://github.com/jasondavies/d3-cloud (repository for davies' d3 cloud)

